Personal cash deposits were £1.33billion, slightly down on May's £1.35billion, while business cash deposits exceeded £1billion for the fourth consecutive month - with £1.11billion deposited against £1.13billion in May. In Northern Ireland, personal cash deposits topped £100million in a month for a second successive time, with £100.2million deposited. The Post Office said personal cash deposits were far higher in Northern Ireland than in Scotland, £90million, or in Wales, £68.4million. Across the UK, personal cash withdrawals were £744million last month, dipping by 3.4 percent from £770million in May. Post Office's Martin Kearsley said: "Postmasters continuing to handle over £3billion a month demonstrates how vital being able to deposit and withdraw cash, securely and conveniently, is for millions of people."